    <div class="chips" id="srcChips"></div>
    <div id="alerts"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- NORTH STAR -->
  <h2 class="sec">Monthly Profitability<span class="rule"></span><span class="pill" id="finRange"></span></h2>
  <div class="cards" id="finance"></div>

  <h2 class="sec">North Star — Concierge Membership<span class="rule"></span><span class="pill" id="nsRange"></span></h2>
  <p class="sec-note" id="nsNote"></p>
  <div class="cards" id="northstar"></div>

  <!-- FUNNEL -->
  <h2 class="sec">Acquisition Funnel<span class="rule"></span><span class="pill" id="funnelRange"></span></h2>
  <p class="sec-note">Month-to-date, each stage from its most truthful source: <b>site visits &amp; booking/phone taps</b> from GA4 · <b>Hint handoffs</b> = outbound clicks that actually reached the mtbakermedical.hint.com booking flow (GA4 outbound-click event) · <b>booked consults</b> and <b>new members</b> from Hint (the EHR — source of truth). Rates show a 95% confidence range because the counts are small; treat the range, not the point, as the truth.</p>
  <div class="small" id="reachLine" style="margin:0 0 8px;padding:8px 12px;background:#F1F4EF;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;font-size:12px"></div>
  <div class="panel"><div class="funnel" id="funnel"></div></div>
  <div class="grid2" style="margin-top:14px">
    <div class="panel">
      <div class="small" style="font-weight:600;font-size:13px;color:var(--forest);margin-bottom:8px">Where prospects vanish <span class="smalltag">permanent watch item</span></div>
      <div id="leakBox" class="small" style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.9"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel">
      <div class="small" style="margin-bottom:6px">Daily booking intent (Book/Call taps) — this month</div>
      <div class="chartbox" style="height:160px"><canvas id="chDaily"></canvas></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="panel" style="margin-top:14px">
    <div class="small" style="font-weight:600;font-size:13px;color:var(--forest);margin-bottom:8px">New members by lead source <span class="small" style="font-weight:400">— self-reported in Hint. At MBM's volume this is the primary attribution truth; GA4 last-click systematically undercredits referrals, GBP and word of mouth.</span></div>
    <div id="memSourceBar"></div>
    <div id="memSourceLegend" class="mixlegend" style="margin-top:8px"></div>
    <div class="small" id="memSourceNote" style="margin-top:8px"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- PAID -->
  <div class="panel" id="leadMagnet" style="margin-bottom:18px"></div>

  <h2 class="sec">Paid Channels<span class="rule"></span><span class="pill" id="paidRange"></span></h2>
  <p class="sec-note"><b>Google Ads is true month-to-date</b> (GAQL, API v21). "Ad-attributed taps" counts GA4-imported booking/phone actions from the <i>All conversions</i> column — immune to the primary/secondary goal misconfiguration that silently zeroed the Conversions column Jul 2–16. Meta &amp; Nextdoor are manual weekly pulls with their own as-of dates.</p>
  <div class="panel" style="margin-top:0;margin-bottom:14px">
    <div class="small" style="font-weight:600;font-size:13px;color:var(--forest);margin-bottom:4px">Channel economics — cost per person delivered to the booking flow <span class="smalltag">the money table</span></div>
    <div id="chanEcon"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="cards" id="paidCards"></div>
  <div class="grid2" style="margin-top:14px">
    <div class="panel"><div class="small" style="margin-bottom:6px">Google Ads campaigns — month-to-date</div><div id="campTable"></div></div>
    <div class="panel"><div class="small" style="margin-bottom:6px">Spend by platform — last 8 months</div><div class="chartbox"><canvas id="chSpend"></canvas></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="panel" style="margin-top:14px" id="socialPanel"></div>

  <!-- GBP -->
  <h2 class="sec">Google Business Profile<span class="rule"></span><span class="pill" id="gbpPill">category experiment</span></h2>
